<br>
With charm as the CC tool you are forced to have more than one chanter, which help their stackability in raids, since you can have only one pet. The problem is that the mobs keep all their abilities while charmed. If the mobs weren't so much more powerful than players no one would complain.<br>
<br>
So they have to lower the power of the mobs but at the same time they have to lower the risk. What if after charm breaks the mob is stunned for 3 secs or snared for 6 secs? This would greatly reduce the risk allowing them to lower the mob statistics while charmed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=casmx>CasmX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#333333>(1/18/03 8:46:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=449.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm solution? (Hopefully not redundant)</span><hr size=1> The best idea I could come up with is make the expierence drop by the margin a charmed pet does. For example, a soloing chanter that lets his pet do all the damage would only recieve a fraction of the what would normally be ungodly exp. maybe 15-20% what it normally would of been. The more damage the charmed pet does, the more exp it takes. This would give incentive for chanters to group, without killing their soloing capabilities. This also gives chanters a choice while in groups whether they think a hasted charm pet would be the way to go, seeing as it would take more xp from the group by doing increased damage.<br>
<br>
As for raid situations, I dont see any problem with a hasted charm pet. It adds DPS to the raid, which is always wanted, yet adds the risk factor seeing if charm breaks, you got a very powerful, hasted add to contend with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 518<br> <font color=#333333>(1/18/03 12:16:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=449.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Not orking either..</span><hr size=1> If you after nerfing the exp chanters get, the idea with charmed pet take exp will not work very well either. <br>
<br>
In the example I described above the charmed pet only kills one of the mobs, the &quot;pet&quot; gets nuked down and the chanter does 100% of the dmg  (since the mob that hurted it was never its pet and is dead).<br>
So instead of getting 12% for those two kills they instead would get 9% (or maybe 7% if they only got 20% of the exp), that is still alot faster than anything else.<br>
I am also sure people will get creative and break charm before first mobs go down and simply root both and nuke both down.<br>
<br>
It wont either fix the abilities to solo minibosses.<br>
<br>
Make mobs more random is in my opinion the best thing, make mobs have small abilities you never really know about until you engage it, just small abilities like unroot/unsnare , unmezzable, uncharmable and summon, atleast on mobs above L57.<br>
This will force you to have atleast a minor group so you can deal with these special ablities. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=449.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=449.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=449.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=449.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=449.topic&index=43><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=449.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=449.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=449.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagiciansto